nested selector and combinators ---->>
------------------------------

combinators->
-----------
isme hamne aagar kisi tag ko id de rkhi h or haam 2 ya 2 se jayada tag pr
 same css likhni h to haam un tag me same class deni hogi then fir css lgani hogi use class pr pr ye 
jayada extra kaam h bar bar jakr same id dena to isme haam combinator ka use krte h 
example --->>
------
#id1,#id2{
    color:"blue";
}
or
.class1,.class2{
    color:"blue";
}
or
child combinator->
---------------

.classname/#idname >tag{    isme parent ke just pass vala child hi slect hoga (pick imidate child)
    color:"blue";
}
or
sibling combinator->
------------------

.classname/#idname + tag{  iski help se haam imidate sibling pr css apply kr skte h 
    color:"blue";              draw h iski agar imidate hoga tbhi css lgegi vrna nhi lgegi
}


or

.classname/#idname ~(tild operator) tag {   ye pure page me se sbhi sibling pr css apply kr dega 
    color:"blue";
}

 nested slector-> 
 ---------------    
 iska use haam jaab krte h jab hme same class ke sirf kuch specific
  tag pr css lgani hoti h puri class pr nhi lgani hoti.
 example->
 .classname  tagname{
    color:"blue";
 }
isme haam kisi bhi tarhe se nesting or combinator use kr skte h jaruri nhi h 
ki vo sirf class pr hi lge vo id pr bhi lag skti h

4.HSL->Hue-Saturation-Lightness 
hsl(hue, saturation, lightness)


Hue -> 0 deg to 360 deg -> 0 to 120 is red
                           120 to 240 is green  0+120+240=360
                           240 to 360 is blue  

  
Saturation->
it is on % value 

Saturation can be described as the intensity of a color. It is a percentage value from 0% to 100%.

100% is full color, no shades of gray.

50% is 50% gray, but you can still see the color.

0% is completely gray; you can no longer see the color.


Lightness
The lightness of a color can be described as how much light you want to give the color, where 0% means no light (dark), 50% means 50% light (neither dark nor light), and 100% means full light.

5.hsla->
hsla(hue, saturation, lightness, alpha)
it is same as hsa but one more extra entity that is 
alpha is opecity 0 to 1.0 and 0 to 100% transparency

range of z-index->

    <div id="login">

            <table>

InRange(in-range) and OutRange(out-of-range)--->
----------------

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        input{
            border-color: black;
        }
        input:in-range{
            background-color: lightgreen;
        }
        input:out-of-range{
            background-color: red;
        }
        input:in-range + .msg::after{
            content:"Valid Age ";
        } input:out-of-range + .msg::after{
            content:"InValid Age ";
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>InRange and OutRange</h1>
    <form action="#">
    Enter Age:    <input type="number" min="10" max="40" value="45">
    <span class="msg"></span>
    <br>
    <span>Age will be in between 10 and 40</span>
    </form>
</body>
</html>

Units in css---->>
-----------

2 types of units ->
1.Absolute units->
     .px-Pixel(smallest units )
     .cm-centimeter / 1cm=37.8px
     .mm-millimeter / 1/10th of cm
     .in-inches  / 1 in-96px 
     .pc-pica / 1/6th of 1in
     .pt-points / 1/72th of 1in

2.Relative units ->

.%-percentage
.em -1em=base size =16px(by default)
.rem-root em -rekative to font size of root elemenet 
.ex-relative to x height of the font 
.vh-viewport height - (defalut height is 1% of visibale area )
.vw-viewport width 
.vmin-viewport min-(relative to smaller dimension % )
.vmax-viewport max (relative to bigger  dimension % )
  viewport -> visival area of the screen  

ex->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        html{
            font-size: 32px ;/*base size change */
        }
        div{
            font-size: 16px;
            /*height: 50vh;*/
            /*width: 50%;50% of body */
            /*width: 50vw;*/
            height: 30vmin;
            width: 50vmax;

            background: 5px solid red;
        }
       .heading_1{
        font-size: 3em;
       } 
       .heading_2{

        /*1 rem is root font size */
        /*font-size: 3em;*/
        font-size: 3rem;
       }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Units </h1>
    <div>
        <h2 class="heading_1">this heading is relative to it's parent </h2>
        <h2 class="heading_2">this heading is relative to root element </h2>
    </div>

Flip Effect using transform and perspective ->
-------------------



<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>flipeffect</title>
    <style>
        .product{
            border: 2px solid red;
            width: 300px;
            height: 600px;
            position: relative;
        }
        img{
            width: 100%;
            
            height: 100%;
        }
        .back{
            position: absolute;
            top: 0px;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            z-index: -1; 
        }
        .back{
            transform: rotateY(-180deg);
        }
        .front{
            height: 100%;
            width: 100%;
        }
        .front,.back{
            transition-duration: 3s;
        }
        .front{
            backface-visibility: hidden;
        }
        .product:hover .front{
            transform: rotateY(180deg);
        }
        .product:hover .back{
            transform: rotateY(0deg);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>flip effect</h1>
    <div class="product">
       <div class="front">
        <img src="images/apple-iphone-12-front.png" alt="">
       </div>
       <div class="back">
        <img src="images/iphoneback.jfif" alt="">
       </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

html->

<!DOCTYPE html>

</head>
<body>
    <h1>3D_Cube</h1>
    <div id="cube">
        <div id="front">front</div>
        <div id="back">back</div>
        <div id="left">left</div>
        <div id="right">right</div>
        <div id="top">top</div>
        <div id="bottom">bottom</div>
    </div>

</body>

css->

#cube{
    position: relative;
    width: 300px;
    height: 300px;
    margin: 230px auto;
    transform-style: preserve-3d;
    transition-duration: 5s;
    animation: cube 10s infinite linear;
}
@keyframes cube{
    0%{
        transform: rotate3d(0,0,0,0deg);
    }
    100%{
        transform: rotate3d(1,1,1,360deg);
    }
    
}
/* #cube:hover {
    transform: rotate(360deg , 360deg);
} */
#cube > div{
    width: 300px;
    height: 300px;
background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
border: 2px solid red;
position: absolute;
color: #fff;
font-size: 70px;
text-transform: capitalize;
transition-duration: 2s;

}
#left{
    transform: rotateY(90deg);
    transform-origin: left;
}
#right{
    transform: rotateY(-90deg);
    transform-origin: right;
}
#top{
    transform: rotateX(-90deg);
    transform-origin: top;
}
#bottom{
    transform: rotateX(90deg);
    transform-origin: bottom;
}
#back{
    /* z-index: -1; */
    transform: translateZ(-300px);
}

Media Queries----->
==============
-RWD-Responsive Web Design 
anotation-@media()
@media(max-width:1200px // breakpoint){//ye code belove the 1200px device ke liye h 
1200 se kaam
    img{
        width:70%;
    }
}

@media(min-width:1200px){
    this is for above 1200px 1200 se jayada vale device ke liye 
    img{
        width:100%;
    }
}

Breakpoints->
by default/standered ->

 XXl -above 1400px
 xl  -above 1200px 
 lg  -above 992px
 md  - above 768px 
 sm   -above 576px
 xs   -below 576px

syntax of media Queries->

@media Screen (min-width:768px) and (max-width:1200px){
    this is valid for above the 768px and below the 1200px 
    body{
        background-color:red;

Where property is one of:

m - for classes that set margin
p - for classes that set padding
Where sides is one of:

t - for classes that set margin-top or padding-top
b - for classes that set margin-bottom or padding-bottom
s - (start) for classes that set margin-left or padding-left in LTR, margin-right or padding-right in RTL
e - (end) for classes that set margin-right or padding-right in LTR, margin-left or padding-left in RTL
x - for classes that set both *-left and *-right
y - for classes that set both *-top and *-bottom
blank - for classes that set a margin or padding on all 4 sides of the element
Where size is one of:

0 - for classes that eliminate the margin or padding by setting it to 0
1 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * .25
2 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * .5
3 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer
4 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * 1.5
5 - (by default) for classes that set the margin or padding to $spacer * 3
auto - for classes that set the margin to auto
(You can add more sizes by adding entries to the $spacers Sass map variable.)
